                                       T-SQL
                                   ============

1.Declaring a Variable
======================

In T-SQL, variables are declared using the DECLARE statement 

syntax:-
======
@variablename datatype(size)

 @a int
 @b varchar(10)
ans:


2.Storing a Value into Variable
================================

In T-SQL, you assign a value to a variable using the SET statement.

syntax:-
======

set @variablename = value;


EX:-
==
declare 
@a int
set @a=80



3.Display a Message (or) Variable Value
=======================================

 To display messages or variable values, use the PRINT statement.

syntax:-
======
PRINT 'message'
PRINT @variablename

Note: When printing numeric variables , convert them to string 
      using CAST or CONVERT.

EX:-
==
declare
@a INT
set @a = 80
print 'Welcome'
print 'Value of a is: ' + CAST(@a AS VARCHAR)



SELECT STATEMENT SYNTAX :-
=======================
SELECT @var1 = col1 , @var2 = col2 , .......
FROM tablename
WHERE condition


